  "user_query": "We want a small Perl-based automated audit to catch common HTML issues in our storefront templates and produce shareable outputs.\n\nUsing the provided files under input/pages and docs/audit_summary.md, please:\n\n1) Write a Perl 5 script at scripts/audit_html.pl that recursively scans all .html files under input/pages and detects the following issues:\n   - missing_or_empty_alt: <img> tags where the alt attribute is missing or the value is an empty string (e.g., alt=\"\").\n   - http_resources: <img src>, <script src>, or <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href> where the URL begins with \"http://\" (flag each such tag).\n   - forms_missing_action: <form> tags with no action attribute.\n   Treat tag and attribute names case-insensitively, and report 1-based line numbers based on the input file as-is. For each file, count occurrences for each issue type and collect the line numbers where the offending tags appear.\n\n2) Write the results to output/audit_report.json with this structure:\n   {\n     \"files\": [\n       {\n         \"path\": \"<file path>\",\n         \"missing_or_empty_alt\": { \"count\": <int>, \"lines\": [<int>, ...] },\n         \"http_resources\": { \"count\": <int>, \"lines\": [<int>, ...] },\n         \"forms_missing_action\": { \"count\": <int>, \"lines\": [<int>, ...] }\n       },\n       ... (one entry per scanned file)\n     ],\n     \"totals\": {\n       \"missing_or_empty_alt\": <int>,\n       \"http_resources\": <int>,\n       \"forms_missing_action\": <int>\n     }\n   }\n   List files in the \"files\" array sorted alphabetically by path for determinism.\n\n3) Edit the existing docs/audit_summary.md by replacing ONLY the content between the markers \"<!-- BEGIN AUTO-AUDIT -->\" and \"<!-- END AUTO-AUDIT -->\" (keep the markers themselves and all other content unchanged) with a concise summary derived from output/audit_report.json. The replaced block must contain:\n   - A line with the exact heading text: Automated HTML Audit Summary\n   - A line with exact keys and totals in this form: Totals: missing_or_empty_alt=X, http_resources=Y, forms_missing_action=Z\n   - A line \"Per-file:\" followed by one bullet per scanned file (alphabetical by path), each bullet in this form:\n     - <path>: missing_or_empty_alt=a, http_resources=b, forms_missing_action=c\n\n4) Draft a plain-text email at output/audit_email_draft.txt that will be sent to QA. The draft must include:\n   - A \"To:\" line with web-qa@example.com\n   - A \"Subject:\" line with: Weekly HTML audit results\n   - A body that restates the same totals and per-file counts as in output/audit_report.json (use the same alphabetical file order), and ends with a single line: Please review by EOD.\n\nNotes and constraints:\n- Use only local files; do not require Internet access.\n- Implement the scanner in Perl (no non-core dependencies required). The JSON, the updated doc section, and the email must be consistent with each other and with the actual findings from input/pages.\n- All output paths are under the workspace as specified: scripts/audit_html.pl, output/audit_report.json, updated docs/audit_summary.md, and output/audit_email_draft.txt. All file paths are relative to the workspace directory.",
